Package: pvsneslib-core
Architecture: amd64
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Recommends: make
Suggests: pvsneslib-examples
Description: SNES homebrew development kit — toolchain and library
 PVSnesLib is a small, open and free development kit for the Nintendo SNES.
 It bundles a complete C toolchain (the 816-tcc compiler plus a pinned WLA DX
 cross-assembler/linker) and a C library, along with asset-conversion tools
 for graphics, tilemaps, and sound (gfx4snes, gfx2snes, smconv, snesbrr,
 snestools, tmx2snes, bin2txt, constify, 816-opt).
 .
 This package ships upstream's pre-built Linux release under
 /usr/lib/pvsneslib. It installs /etc/profile.d/pvsneslib.sh which exports
 PVSNESLIB_HOME=/usr/lib/pvsneslib. Projects are built by writing a Makefile
 that includes $PVSNESLIB_HOME/devkitsnes/snes_rules and running make — the
 bundled tools are invoked through that rules file, not from $PATH (which is
 why nothing is symlinked into /usr/bin).
 .
 Install pvsneslib-examples for the bundled sample projects, or the pvsneslib
 metapackage to pull in both.

Package: pvsneslib-examples
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends},
 pvsneslib-core (>= ${source:Version})
Recommends: make
Description: SNES homebrew development kit — example projects
 The bundled PVSnesLib sample projects (graphics, sound, input, sprites, maps,
 and more), installed under /usr/lib/pvsneslib/snes-examples so they resolve
 against PVSNESLIB_HOME=/usr/lib/pvsneslib.
 .
 Each example is built by running make inside its directory after sourcing
 /etc/profile.d/pvsneslib.sh (or exporting PVSNESLIB_HOME). This is the
 quickest way to confirm the toolchain works and to learn the API.
 .
 This package is architecture-independent (sources and assets only); the
 toolchain it needs lives in pvsneslib-core.

Package: pvsneslib
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends},
 pvsneslib-core (>= ${source:Version}),
 pvsneslib-examples (>= ${source:Version})
Description: SNES homebrew development kit (complete)
 PVSnesLib is a small, open and free development kit for the Nintendo SNES,
 providing a C toolchain, library, and asset-conversion tools.
 .
 This metapackage installs the complete kit: the toolchain and library
 (pvsneslib-core) plus the sample projects (pvsneslib-examples).
